cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is about salient object detection, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a learning-based framework, which suggests that it may belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of feature spaces and scales, which are common in multimedia (cs.MM) and neural networks (cs.NE).
